obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line 7
  line `he shall be liable, on conviction, to imprisonment for a period not exceeding seven years, with or without`
  line `labour, or to fine, or to both.`
  line `XVII. Penalt y for other wilful damage. — Whoever damages any public embankment by making any`
  line `dam or other obstruction for the purpose of diverting or opposing the current of an embanked river without`
  line `the permission of the officer in immediate charge of the embankment, or by refusing or neglecting to remove`
  line `any such dam or obstruction at the proper season, or by cutting or otherwise altering the banks of any`
  line `embanked river, or by removing the earth from such embankment, or by grazing or tethering any cattle or`
  line `animals on any such embankment, or by driving stakes into or cutting or rooting out grass growing on, such`
  line `embankment, or by any other wilful act destroys or diminishes the efficiency of such embankment shall be`
  line `liable, on conviction before a Magistrate, to simple imprisonment for a term not e xceeding six months, or`
  line `to a fine not exceeding two hundred rupees, or to both.`
  line `XVIII. Jurisdiction of Deputy or Assistant Magistrate under this Act. — Any Deputy or Assistant`
  line `Magistrate may take cognizance of offences under this Act, and may punish offende rs to the extent of the`
  line `power conferred upon him by the Regulations of the Bengal Code, and by the Acts of the Governor General`
  line `of India in Council with respect to the punishment of misdemeanors.`
  line `XIX. Provision of Section XIII. Regulation XX. 1817 extended to this Act. — The p rovision of`
  line `Section XIII. Regulation XX. Of 1817 shall extend to any charge or information of the offences specified`
  line `in Section XVI. of this Act; and Darogahs and other Police Officers shall enquire into such offences in the`
  line `mode and s ubject to the provisions therein prescribed.`
  line `XX. Right of appeal. — All sentences and orders passed by a Magistrate, Deputy Magistrate or`
  line `Assistant Magistrate under this Act shall be appealable, subject to the general provisions which regulate`
  line appeals.
  line `21. Interpretation. — In the construction of this Act, words importing the singular number only shall`
  line `include the plural, and words importing the plural number only shall include the singular: words importing`
  line `the masculine gender only shall include females; the word “ Collector ” shall mean any Collector, Deputy`
  line `Collector or other Revenue Officer in independent charge of any district or portion of a district.`
  line ________
